textBody:
Iron Duke may refer to:

People:
* Fernando Álvarez de Toledo, 3rd Duke of Alba (1507–1582), a Spanish noble, general, and diplomat
* Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington (1769–1852), a British soldier and statesman
* Luís Alves de Lima e Silva, Duke of Caxias (1803–1880), a Brazilian army officer and politician
* William Mark Duke (1879–1971), an Archbishop of Vancouver
* John F. Thompson  (1920–1965), a U.S. politician
* Irvin Khoza (born 1948), a South African football administrator

Artistic works:
* The Iron Duke (film), 1934 film starring George Arliss about the First Duke of Wellington
* The Iron Duke (novel), a pulp fiction, pre-WWII adventure story written by L. Ron Hubbard

Ship names:
* , a British Royal Navy shipname
* HMS Iron Duke (1870), a battleship sold for scrap in 1906
* HMS Iron Duke (1912), the fleet flagship at the Battle of Jutland
* HMS Iron Duke (F234), a Type 23 frigate launched in 1991

Locomotive names:
* GWR Iron Duke Class, a class of locomotive built by the Great Western Railway in England
* Iron Duke, a GWR 3031 Class locomotive built in 1892

Miscellaneous:
* Duke Blue Devils football, especially during their 1938 undefeated season
* Iron Duke engine, a 2.5 L I4 piston engine made by General Motors
* Iron Duke, South Australia, an iron ore mining settlement near Whyalla
* The Iron Dukes, the name the 2nd Battalion 37th Armored Regiment
